!! Example CASE operator usage

```sql
SELECT name,
    CASE WHEN (monthlymaintenance > 100) THEN
      'expensive'
    ELSE
      'cheap'
    END AS cost
    FROM cd.facilities;
```

Will return something like this:

| !name | !cost    |
|Court1 |cheap |
|Court2 | expensive|